The article is a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at Barnard College in New York. In her speech, she emphasizes the importance of electing Kathy Hochul as the next governor of New York. She talks about the accomplishments of the current administration, such as extending the child tax credit, passing tax cuts for parents, investing in climate crisis solutions, appointing a Black woman to the Supreme Court, and canceling student loan debt. Harris also discusses the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights and the need for strong leaders at the state level to protect reproductive rights, voting rights, and LGBTQ+ rights. She highlights the role of the United States as a model for democracy and the importance of defending democratic values. Harris urges the audience to vote and fight for the principles and ideals of the nation.